The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Footballer son
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Footballer son
                            
	Calcutta, May 13: Rana Banerjee, son of former Mohun Bagan footballer Badru Banerjee, has committed suicide by consuming poison, police said. He was 40.        
	Rana died in Shambhunath Pandit Hospital after he was taken there from his Dhakuria house. The police said debts could be the reason for the suicide.                                                                                                                                                                         
